Sir, you wrote the Americans
with Disabilities Act.

11:36.520 --> 11:39.880
That's a big friggin deal.

11:39.960 --> 11:42.400
Gentlemen,
the National Council on Disability,

11:42.400 --> 11:46.000
with nine Presidentially
and Congressionally appointed members,

11:46.080 --> 11:49.840
carries a statutory mission
to advise the President,

11:49.920 --> 11:52.760
his administration, Congress and federal

11:52.760 --> 11:58.480
agencies on all policy matters impacting
people with disabilities. The health

11:58.480 --> 12:02.960
and well-being of people with disabilities
have long been ignored in this country.

12:03.040 --> 12:05.520
This occurs despite the existence

12:05.520 --> 12:10.440
of an overwhelming body of studies
and reports that unequivocally document

12:10.520 --> 12:14.800
the significant and continuing
prevalence of health disparities that

12:14.880 --> 12:18.800
exist between people with disabilities
and our non-disabled counterparts.

12:18.840 --> 12:23.880
The National Council on Disability
was fighting for federal legislation

12:23.960 --> 12:28.200
to protect the rights of persons with disabilities

12:28.280 --> 12:31.280
since its inception. NCD has worked to develop

12:31.320 --> 12:35.960
a health equity framework
to provide policymakers in Congress

12:36.040 --> 12:40.000
and in the administration with a blueprint
to take action.

12:40.080 --> 12:43.720
The adoption of enforceable medical
diagnostic equipment standards

12:43.800 --> 12:49.320
is just one step towards health equity
for persons with mobility disabilities

12:49.400 --> 12:54.720
and is just one component of NCD's
pursuit of health equity for all people

12:54.840 --> 12:59.960
with disabilities--for an all of government
approach to address health disparities.

13:00.040 --> 13:03.240
The framework was one year
in the making with the input of our

13:03.240 --> 13:07.600
then-Council members, members
of the disability community and a dream

13:07.600 --> 13:11.640
team of 14 advisors
comprised of health care disparities

13:11.640 --> 13:15.880
researchers, physicians
caring for people with disabilities,

13:15.960 --> 13:19.440
health care and disability law professors,
among others.

13:19.480 --> 13:22.240
It's a matter of attaining
and maintaining good health.

13:22.240 --> 13:23.760
It's critically

13:23.760 --> 13:28.160
important for everyone, but more so for persons with disabilities.

13:28.240 --> 13:32.680
It's truly the predicate to our ability to live, our ability to learn,

13:32.760 --> 13:38.080
and our ability to work and earn. Into the forefront of discussions

13:38.080 --> 13:42.840
that are taking place in medical schools
and perhaps at the associations here.

13:42.920 --> 13:46.960
I have to impart with
your, our house is on fire.

13:47.040 --> 13:48.080
The issues that we're

13:48.080 --> 13:52.400
talking about here, when individuals like me

13:52.480 --> 13:55.320
can't get weighed at medical appointments
because there's

13:55.320 --> 13:58.320
no wheelchair accessible weight skills,
when we don't get transferred

13:58.440 --> 14:02.560
onto examination tables
for full physical examination

14:02.640 --> 14:07.040
because of the inability
or the unwillingness of providers to do so.

14:07.120 --> 14:11.640
And then we see a heightened percentage
of people with spinal cord injuries

14:11.720 --> 14:16.280
and mobility disabilities being diagnosed
with colon cancer because they're simply

14:16.280 --> 14:20.640
not being checked or prostate cancer
because they're simply not being checked.

14:20.720 --> 14:24.000
We don't have time for polite

14:24.080 --> 14:27.800
conversations in your respective schools.

14:27.800 --> 14:31.200
We need some action,
and that has to happen.

14:31.200 --> 14:37.880
And so I impart to you
that our house is on fire

14:37.960 --> 14:46.280
and these issues need resolution.

14:46.360 --> 14:47.200
Let's remember that

14:47.200 --> 14:51.760
disability is a natural part of the human condition.

14:51.840 --> 14:52.200
Let us

14:52.200 --> 14:56.640
remember that disability is not a characteristic that stands alone,

14:56.720 --> 15:00.080
but it is one that intersects
with all other aspects

15:00.320 --> 15:04.880
of a person's identity,
such as age, race, ethnicity,

15:04.960 --> 15:09.880
income level, sexual orientation,
gender identity and religion.

15:09.960 --> 15:14.440
Let us recommit to shaping a future
in which all members of this beautiful

15:14.440 --> 15:18.240
community can have and enjoy full rights,

15:18.320 --> 15:20.680
free from discrimination

15:20.680 --> 15:23.960
to live self-directed, independent lives.

15:24.040 --> 15:26.720
To achieve our full potential.

15:26.720 --> 15:30.000
Achieving our full potential is only possible

15:30.080 --> 15:57.040
