01:37:15.480 --> 01:37:21.000
And so we did the same thing in PROWAG,
and stayed consistent with ADAG.

01:37:21.080 --> 01:37:24.720
at languages such as changes in local
versus vertical surface

01:37:24.720 --> 01:37:26.440
discontinuities that we were referring to.

01:37:26.440 --> 01:37:30.400
So you'll see those changes really about consistency.

01:37:30.480 --> 01:37:33.880
Another change we made was,

01:37:33.960 --> 01:37:37.240
I talked about the detectable warning surfaces at driveways.

01:37:37.320 --> 01:37:41.760
We expanded the treatment options
for roundabouts.

01:37:41.840 --> 01:37:45.640
So in the proposed rule,
there was only one option for roundabouts.

01:37:45.640 --> 01:37:50.080
But in talking to transportation
engineers and others in industry,

01:37:50.160 --> 01:37:53.720
we found that there was a need to expand
the treatment options

01:37:53.800 --> 01:37:59.200
and hopefully further research will refine
if there is indeed some options

01:37:59.200 --> 01:38:03.280
that are a lot more accessible
than others.

01:38:03.360 --> 01:38:05.680
We added visual contrast

01:38:05.680 --> 01:38:09.600
requirements for stairs,
and that is a new requirement.

01:38:09.600 --> 01:38:14.280
There was an overwhelming request
for us to make that a requirement.

01:38:14.280 --> 01:38:17.880
So at top of the stairs, tread or landing,

01:38:17.960 --> 01:38:22.200
there needs to be a visual contrast
as best just really

01:38:22.200 --> 01:38:26.680
a high level of what we've added,
what's in the new rule.

01:38:26.760 --> 01:38:30.120
so the Access Board, we finalized the  guidelines

01:38:30.200 --> 01:38:34.000
and when we finalize a set of guidelines,
there is a mandate

01:38:34.000 --> 01:38:39.480
for the enforcing agencies
to adopt them as standards.

01:38:39.600 --> 01:38:41.520
They can increase the accessibility,

01:38:41.520 --> 01:38:45.360
but they cannot adopt something
that's less than what we've required.

01:38:45.440 --> 01:38:46.920
And so that would be the next step.

01:38:46.920 --> 01:38:51.080
We don't do it enforcing
other than at ABA facilities.

01:38:51.160 --> 01:38:55.920
So in order for PROWAG to be enforceable under the ADA,

01:38:55.920 --> 01:39:00.160
it would need to be adopted by Department,
Justice Department, Transportation

01:39:00.240 --> 01:39:01.200
and ABA.

