01:44:03.000 --> 01:44:04.800
the goals underneath

01:44:04.800 --> 01:44:08.760
enabling safe and accessible
air travel were the following.

01:44:08.840 --> 01:44:10.920
We wanted to develop

01:44:10.920 --> 01:44:14.320
an advanced research roadmap

01:44:14.400 --> 01:44:17.120
building off of the Access Board

01:44:17.120 --> 01:44:21.400
and the Transportation Research Board's

01:44:21.480 --> 01:44:22.920
report on the feasibility of

01:44:22.920 --> 01:44:26.640
wheelchair
security systems on passenger aircraft,

01:44:26.720 --> 01:44:28.760
which will support

01:44:28.760 --> 01:44:32.920
future rulemaking by the department,
which would then make it a rule

01:44:32.920 --> 01:44:38.840
that wheelchair spot
be provided on airplanes.

01:44:38.920 --> 01:44:39.840
So the next thing

01:44:39.840 --> 01:44:42.840
was to ensure rulemaking, to ensure

01:44:42.880 --> 01:44:46.400
safe accommodations for air travelers
with disabilities using a wheelchair.

01:44:46.400 --> 01:44:52.000
So we have an NPRM
that will be coming out

01:44:52.080 --> 01:44:56.800
in the next few weeks

01:44:56.880 --> 01:44:59.360
that will address

01:44:59.360 --> 01:45:02.720
both the mishandling of wheelchairs

01:45:02.800 --> 01:45:05.800
and the

01:45:06.000 --> 01:45:09.840
unsafe handling of people with
disabilities, which results in injuries.

01:45:09.920 --> 01:45:12.520
So the rule is going to make it a pro se

01:45:12.520 --> 01:45:15.520
violation

01:45:15.640 --> 01:45:16.680
of the Air Carriers

01:45:16.680 --> 01:45:20.640
Access Act
if a wheelchair is damaged by an airline.

01:45:20.720 --> 01:45:22.440
Right now, the wording is a little fuzzy.

01:45:22.440 --> 01:45:26.400
So the airlines can deny that they violated the Act.

01:45:26.440 --> 01:45:29.440
This will make it a pro se violation

01:45:29.640 --> 01:45:31.600
And so

01:45:31.680 --> 01:45:33.840
at that point,

01:45:33.840 --> 01:45:37.840
they'll just automatically be found guilty
of violating the Air Carrier Access Act

01:45:37.920 --> 01:45:41.600
and then will be subject to fines.

01:45:41.680 --> 01:45:43.440
We also

01:45:43.440 --> 01:45:47.240
