02:08:59.360 --> 02:08:59.760
So to

02:08:59.760 --> 02:09:02.800
talk about the ADA's transportation provisions,

02:09:02.800 --> 02:09:07.560
I'll mention that Title II of the ADA applies to public entities.

02:09:07.640 --> 02:09:10.000
It also applies to Amtrak.

02:09:10.000 --> 02:09:12.840
So folks don't realize Amtrak falls under Title II

02:09:12.840 --> 02:09:15.840
of the ADA as a public entity.

02:09:16.000 --> 02:09:21.040
Title III of the ADA applies to public
accommodations or private entities.

02:09:21.120 --> 02:09:26.560
That includes private entities
that provide transportation services,

02:09:26.640 --> 02:09:31.120
and both US Department of Transportation
and the Department of Justice

02:09:31.200 --> 02:09:36.400
have issued regulations under the ADA. Kelly covered a lot of that.

02:09:36.480 --> 02:09:39.080
DOT’s ADA regulations

02:09:39.080 --> 02:09:44.080
that are relevant to taxi companies
and TNCs can be found at Title 49

02:09:44.120 --> 02:09:48.280
of the Code of Federal Regulations, in Parts

02:09:48.360 --> 02:09:52.080
37 and Part 38.

02:09:52.160 --> 02:09:56.440
Part 38 has vehicle specifications which

02:09:56.520 --> 02:10:01.240
would relate to the types of accessibility
requirements for vehicles.

02:10:01.320 --> 02:10:05.920
Part 37 contains some broader
nondiscrimination protections.

02:10:06.000 --> 02:10:10.000
DOJ is responsible for enforcing Title III

02:10:10.000 --> 02:10:15.000
of the ADA and Parts 37 and 38

02:10:15.080 --> 02:10:19.120
of Title 49 the Code of Federal Regulations.

02:10:19.200 --> 02:10:23.280
We've done that, and the examples
I'm about to give relate

02:10:23.520 --> 02:10:29.080
