in these regulatory

02:13:06.240 --> 02:13:10.520
provisions would be something bigger
than an eight person band.

02:13:10.520 --> 02:13:12.240
And it has to be a new vehicle.

02:13:12.240 --> 02:13:15.360
These are purchased
by this kind of transportation entity,

02:13:15.360 --> 02:13:19.360
whether it's a fixed route or demand,
responsive.

02:13:19.800 --> 02:13:25.080
So that's the regulatory and legal background.
The Chariot Transit, Inc., matter

02:13:25.160 --> 02:13:28.600
involved a private transportation company
that provided a fixed route

02:13:28.600 --> 02:13:30.440
and on demand service.

02:13:30.440 --> 02:13:34.080
It also leased or owned vehicles
that were not automobiles

02:13:34.080 --> 02:13:37.080
and did hold more than eight passengers.

02:13:37.080 --> 02:13:41.760
The United States alleged
that Chariot did not comply with the ADA

02:13:41.760 --> 02:13:45.760
obligations to provide equivalent service

02:13:45.840 --> 02:13:48.680
or to have its vehicles be accessible

02:13:48.680 --> 02:13:51.360
by doing things
like telling people with disabilities

02:13:51.360 --> 02:13:55.480
that the company only provided service
to individuals who use wheelchairs

02:13:55.560 --> 02:13:59.640
if they could transfer to a seat
and if there was space for the wheelchair

02:13:59.640 --> 02:14:02.640
that did not take the seat
of another passenger.

02:14:02.680 --> 02:14:04.960
Those who required an accessible vehicle

02:14:04.960 --> 02:14:08.440
would only be provided
accessible resources in the region.

02:14:08.520 --> 02:14:12.280
And so DOJ went into
a settlement agreement

02:14:12.280 --> 02:14:16.560
after reaching out to this company,
the company agreed to begin operating

02:14:16.560 --> 02:14:20.480
sufficient accessible vehicles
to provide passengers with disabilities

02:14:20.480 --> 02:14:24.760
with equivalent service, to not require
passengers with disabilities.

02:14:24.760 --> 02:14:28.840
to not require passengers with disabilities to have a different manner for booking vehicles from other passengers,

02:14:29.000 --> 02:14:32.680
to train the company's
employees on the ADA requirements,

02:14:32.760 --> 02:14:37.120
including requirements for accessible
vehicles and equivalent services,

02:14:37.200 --> 02:14:40.200
and to pay the United States
the civil penalty.

02:14:40.320 --> 02:14:44.280
That was from around
seven or eight years ago.

02:14:44.280 --> 02:14:46.600
Chariot Transit Inc.

02:14:46.680 --> 02:14:49.680
A little bit more recently in 2020, DOJ

02:14:49.680 --> 02:14:53.880
