02:50:01.800 --> 02:50:02.880
PUBLIC COMMENT: Good afternoon.

02:50:02.880 --> 02:50:06.320
I'll be sharing anecdotes
gathered from DREDF friends and colleagues,

02:50:06.320 --> 02:50:11.040
as well as concerning trends,
regarding experiences with paratransit.

02:50:11.120 --> 02:50:15.120
Paratransit remains a critical option
for people with disabilities.

02:50:15.200 --> 02:50:18.840
Unfortunately, long and often
unpredictable wait times for pick up

02:50:18.840 --> 02:50:20.160
remain an issue.

02:50:20.160 --> 02:50:23.320
In addition, we have heard that adequate
time is not being given

02:50:23.320 --> 02:50:26.520
for passengers to get to the vehicle
that is picking them up.

02:50:26.600 --> 02:50:30.360
And when a paratransit trip
is a shared trip, it can be a 20 minute

02:50:30.360 --> 02:50:34.200
trip easily turns into a three hour
or even longer trip.

02:50:34.280 --> 02:50:38.040
These long and unpredictable wait times
combined with shared rides can lead to

02:50:38.040 --> 02:50:43.240
riders being late for or losing their jobs
or canceled medical appointments.

02:50:43.320 --> 02:50:43.920
We have heard

02:50:43.920 --> 02:50:48.160
instances of drivers taking actions
that lead to an unsafe atmosphere.

02:50:48.240 --> 02:50:50.160
Recently, a paratransit

02:50:50.160 --> 02:50:54.200
threatened to call the police when a rider
had difficulty leaving the vehicle.

02:50:54.280 --> 02:50:57.240
The transit agency
sent a warning to the rider rather

02:50:57.240 --> 02:51:01.440
than taking steps to ensure their safety
and well-being, that if it's concerned

02:51:01.440 --> 02:51:04.960
with any transit policy
which leads to unnecessary interactions

02:51:04.960 --> 02:51:09.000
between police and disabled passengers,
especially disabled black and brown

02:51:09.000 --> 02:51:12.960
passengers are disproportionately harmed
in these interactions.

02:51:13.040 --> 02:51:16.080
We have also heard on the flip side
that the social interaction

02:51:16.080 --> 02:51:19.320
between the driver and passenger
can provide an important social

02:51:19.320 --> 02:51:23.320
connection for riders
who might otherwise be isolated.

02:51:23.400 --> 02:51:25.000
Regarding use of wheelchair accessible

02:51:25.000 --> 02:51:28.320
taxis and transportation
network companies or TNCs.

02:51:28.400 --> 02:51:31.360
As I just noted,
Uber and Lyft only provide wheelchair

02:51:31.360 --> 02:51:35.440
accessible vehicles or WAV service in select markets.
In cities where WAV

02:51:35.440 --> 02:51:36.600
service is not offered.

02:51:36.600 --> 02:51:40.720
Lyft provides a link on their website
to paratransit options in those markets.

02:51:40.960 --> 02:51:45.880
However, the link is broken and takes
user to a page that is no longer active.

02:51:45.960 --> 02:51:48.360
Many transit agencies partner witnesses,

02:51:48.360 --> 02:51:51.640
taxi companies to provide alternatives to paratransit.

02:51:51.720 --> 02:51:54.600
Unfortunately, we hear that
there are not enough WAV vehicles

02:51:54.600 --> 02:51:59.560
to meet demand. In Washington DC,
where WMATA partners with TNCs and taxis

02:51:59.560 --> 02:52:03.360
to provide a free on demand alternative
that is not a shared ride.

02:52:03.440 --> 02:52:06.760
We have heard that the service
does not provide Uber WAV vehicles

02:52:06.760 --> 02:52:10.400
because the staff would rather leave
the limited WAV vehicles on the streets

02:52:10.400 --> 02:52:14.400
for wheelchair users
who want to hail a ride in real time.

02:52:14.480 --> 02:52:15.240
In many areas

02:52:15.240 --> 02:52:18.240
where TNCs operate, transit
ridership has decreased

02:52:18.280 --> 02:52:22.200
and the numbers of taxis and wheelchair
accessible taxis has decreased as well.

02:52:22.200 --> 02:52:25.520
There are many studies
that show this that decreases in transit.

02:52:25.520 --> 02:52:27.560
Ridership can lead to cuts in transit
hours

02:52:27.560 --> 02:52:31.400
and routes can also lead
to cuts in paratransit service areas.

02:52:31.480 --> 02:52:34.680
In addition, New York City
recently implemented policies

02:52:34.680 --> 02:52:38.200
pushing to make taxi and TNC fleets
all electric.

02:52:38.280 --> 02:52:40.960
The current requirement
allows for gas vehicles

02:52:40.960 --> 02:52:44.320
to still be operated
if they are wheelchair accessible.

02:52:44.400 --> 02:52:48.640
DREDF is advocating for any alternative
fuel or cleaner transportation mode

02:52:48.720 --> 02:52:52.320
to also be fully accessible,
including to wheelchair users.

02:52:52.400 --> 02:52:55.680
Finally, Waymo is currently providing
autonomous on demand

02:52:55.680 --> 02:52:58.200
commercial service,
similar to Uber and Lyft.

02:52:58.200 --> 02:53:00.160
They claim their AVs are safer.

02:53:00.160 --> 02:53:03.720
